Matplotlib's open source code includes a SECURITY.md file that is a short document featuring a link to report vulnerabilities as well as a table that depicts what versions are currently without any kind of vulnerabilities and are safe to use.


Version	Supported
3.6.x	✅
3.5.x	✅
3.4.x	❌
3.3.x	❌
< 3.3	❌

Reporting a Vulnerability
Security Vulnerability Reporting: https://tidelift.com/docs/security. Tidelift will coordinate the fix and disclosure.

Upon using an external software, the total vulnerabilities currently were 0.

The documentation also supports a separate documentation page for the latest stable version. Branches also exist for separate versions and any security issues may be catered there.
